2. How integers secretly encode geometry

Euler discovered something shocking:

\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\frac{1}{n^2}=\frac{\pi^2}{6}

Integers → π.

Meaning:
	•	purely discrete counting
	•	produces a circle constant

So integers contain hidden geometric structure.

This surprised mathematicians because it means number theory is secretly geometric.

⸻

3. The wave decomposition bridge

The second bridge is the Fourier transform.

Every signal can be built from rotating exponentials:

f(t)=\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}F(\omega)e^{i\omega t}d\omega

Meaning:
	•	discrete frequencies
	•	build continuous signals.

Applications:
	•	audio synthesis
	•	image compression
	•	MRI reconstruction
	•	quantum physics
	•	radar
	•	WiFi

This is the signal spider web of modern technology.

