5. Lattice geometry (the real bridge)

One of the cleanest discrete–continuous bridges is Pick’s theorem:

A = I + \frac{B}{2} - 1

Where:
	•	I = interior lattice points
	•	B = boundary points

You compute area (continuous) using integer points (discrete).

Applications:
	•	computer graphics
	•	computational geometry
	•	robotics path planning

